  "texts": [
    "Therefore, the results reported in the Spider leaderboard are biased toward databases with small schemas and NL questions written in the schema vocabulary, which is not what one finds in real-world databases.",
    "The Spider dataset has modified versions, such as Spider-Syn and Spider DK.",
    "In the Spider-Syn (GAN et al., 2021) dataset, words and phrases are replaced with synonyms and emphasizes the importance of maintaining accurate schema linking mechanisms.",
    "It comprises 5,672 questions and aims at leveraging common word substitutions related to schema items and values to enhance the accuracy of models in translating natural language questions into SQL queries.",
    "The Spider DK dataset (GAN; CHEN; PURVER, 2021) addresses testing how well Text-to-SQL tools deal with domain knowledge."
  ],
